rbnSubscriberActiveMib.name: rbnSubscriberActiveMib

revisions.description: Changed the following not-accessible objects to read-only rbnSubsActiveIpAddrType rbnSubsActiveIpAddr rbnSubsActiveIpPfxLen

Add rbnSubsIPv4OctetsSent rbnSubsIPv4OctetsReceived, rbnSubsIPv6OctetsSent, rbnSubsIPv6OctetsReceived, rbnSubsIPv4PktsSent, rbnSubsIPv4PktsReceived, rbnSubsIPv6PktsSent, rbnSubsIPv6PktsReceived, rbnSubsIPv4McastOctetsSent, rbnSubsIPv4McastOctetsReceived, rbnSubsIPv6McastOctetsSent, rbnSubsIPv6McastOctetsReceived, rbnSubsIPv4McastPktsSent, rbnSubsIPv4McastPktsReceived, rbnSubsIPv6McastPktsSent, rbnSubsIPv6McastPktsReceived to RbnSubsStatsEntry table rbnSubsServiceIPv4VolumeOctetsIn, rbnSubsServiceIPv4VolumeOctetsOut, rbnSubsServiceIPv6VolumeOctetsIn, rbnSubsServiceIPv6VolumeOctetsOut, rbnSubsServiceIPv4VolumePktsIn, rbnSubsServiceIPv4VolumePktsOut, rbnSubsServiceIPv6VolumePktsIn, rbnSubsServiceIPv6VolumePktsOut to RbnSubsServiceVolumeEntry table

Add rbnSubsMaxSupportedSessions, rbnSubsLicensedSessions, rbnSubsActiveSessions, and rbnSubsCapacityPercentageUsed. Defined rbnSubsCompliance5 and rbnSubsLicenseGroup for compliance. Deprecated rbnSubsCompliance4 and obsoleted rbnSubsCompliance3.
Add rbnSubsConfigErrorEvent notification along with the associated objects. Defined rbnSubsNotifyObjectGroup and rbnSubsNotifyGroup for compliance.

Add rbnSubsServiceVolumeTable and rbnSubsServicesTable along with associated objects. Defined rbnSubsCompliance4 and rbnSubsServicesGroup for compliance. Deprecated rbnSubsCompliance3 and obsoleted rbnSubsCompliance2.
Add rbnSubsActiveNasPortType and rbnSubsActiveMediumType to RbnSubsActiveEntry. Update conformance objects appropriately.
Add objects rbnSubsReauthName and rbnSubsReauthSessionId. These objects supercede the objects defined in the RBN-SUBSCRIBER-REAUTH-MIB.
Add rbnSubsActiveResend to rbnSubsActiveEntry. Add rbnSubsProfileCountTable with objects rbnSubsProfileName and rbnSubsProfileCount. Updated compliance and groups to reflect new objects.

rbnSubscriberActiveMib.contactinfo: Redback Networks, Inc. Postal: 300 Holger Way San Jose, CA 95134 USA Phone: +1 408 750 5000 Fax: +1 408 750 5599 E-mail: mib-info@redback.com
rbnSubscriberActiveMib.description: Defines the objects necessary to support the management of active subscribers in Redback product family. All mib objects, except rbnSubsCntxtCountTable, defined in the module are viewed within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).

rbnSubsActiveTable.name: rbnSubsActiveTable
rbnSubsActiveTable.description: This table contains subscriber sessions which have been authenticated on an circuit.

rbnSubsActiveEntry.name: rbnSubsActiveEntry
rbnSubsActiveEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnSubsActiveTable.

rbnSubsActiveName.name: rbnSubsActiveName
rbnSubsActiveName.description: The name identifying this entry. An entry configured by other means may have been given a name whose length is greater than 80. Names which exceed this length are not accessible via SNMP operations.

rbnSubsActiveSessionId.name: rbnSubsActiveSessionId
rbnSubsActiveSessionId.reference: Rigney, C., RADIUS Accounting, RFC 2866, June 2000
rbnSubsActiveSessionId.description: A value that uniquely identifies an active subscriber session. If RADIUS is being used to configure/authenticate subscribers, this value will appear in the RADIUS Acct-Session-Id attribute.

rbnSubsActiveCircuitDescr.name: rbnSubsActiveCircuitDescr
rbnSubsActiveCircuitDescr.description: A string which provides identifying information (e.g slot/port) of the circuit the subscriber is using.

rbnSubsActiveStartTime.name: rbnSubsActiveStartTime
rbnSubsActiveStartTime.description: The time when the subscriber became active.

rbnSubsActiveClear.name: rbnSubsActiveClear
rbnSubsActiveClear.description: Setting this value to 'true' will clear the active subscriber session. In the case of PPP, the PPP state machinery attempts to renegotiate and re-authenticate a new session with the remote peer on the circuit. In the case of RFC 1483 encapsulated circuits the session is brought down and then back up and an attempt is made to re-authenticate the subscriber. An SNMP get operation always returns 'false'

rbnSubsActiveResend.name: rbnSubsActiveResend
rbnSubsActiveResend.description: Setting this value to 'true' will cause a resend of the Radius acct-start packet. An SNMP get operation always returns 'false'

rbnSubsActiveNasPortType.name: rbnSubsActiveNasPortType
rbnSubsActiveNasPortType.reference: Rigney, C., Rubens, A., Simpson, W., and Willens, S., Remote Authentication Dial In User Service (RADIUS), RFC 2865, June 2000
rbnSubsActiveNasPortType.description: The RADIUS attribute NAS-Port-Type which indicates the type of the physical port which is authenticating the user.

rbnSubsActiveMediumType.name: rbnSubsActiveMediumType
rbnSubsActiveMediumType.description: The medium type of the NAS-Port.

rbnSubsActiveResendSvcAcct.name: rbnSubsActiveResendSvcAcct
rbnSubsActiveResendSvcAcct.description: Setting this value to 'true' will cause a resend of the Radius acct-start packet for all services associated with the active subscriber session. An SNMP get operation always returns 'false'

rbnSubsActiveIpTable.name: rbnSubsActiveIpTable
rbnSubsActiveIpTable.description: This table contains IP addresses used by active subscribers.

rbnSubsActiveIpEntry.name: rbnSubsActiveIpEntry
rbnSubsActiveIpEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnSubsActiveIpTable.

rbnSubsActiveAddr.name: rbnSubsActiveAddr
rbnSubsActiveAddr.description: The host IP address of the active subscriber.

rbnSubsActiveSessionTable.name: rbnSubsActiveSessionTable
rbnSubsActiveSessionTable.description: This table contains active subscriber sessions which have been authenticated on an circuit.

rbnSubsActiveSessionEntry.name: rbnSubsActiveSessionEntry
rbnSubsActiveSessionEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnSubsActiveSessionTable.

rbnSubsActiveSessionSubscriberName.name: rbnSubsActiveSessionSubscriberName
rbnSubsActiveSessionSubscriberName.description: The subscriber name associated with this session.

rbnSubsActiveSessionPointer.name: rbnSubsActiveSessionPointer
rbnSubsActiveSessionPointer.description: A pointer to the row in rbnSubsActiveTable to which this session belongs. May be {0 0} if there is no such row.

rbnSubsActiveIpAddrTable.name: rbnSubsActiveIpAddrTable
rbnSubsActiveIpAddrTable.description: This table contains IPv4/IPv6 addresses used by active subscriber sessions.

rbnSubsActiveIpAddrEntry.name: rbnSubsActiveIpAddrEntry
rbnSubsActiveIpAddrEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnSubsActiveIpAddrTable.

rbnSubsActiveIpAddr.name: rbnSubsActiveIpAddr
rbnSubsActiveIpAddr.reference: [RFC4291] IP Version 6 Addressing Architectur [RFC4632] Classless Inter-domain Routing (CIDR): The Internet Address Assignment and Aggregation Plan
rbnSubsActiveIpAddr.description: The address prefix. The address type of this object is specified in rbnSubsActiveIpAddrType. The length of this object is the standard length for objects of that type (4 or 16 bytes). Any bits after rbnSubsActiveIpPfxLen must be zero.

rbnSubsActiveIpPfxLen.name: rbnSubsActiveIpPfxLen
rbnSubsActiveIpPfxLen.description: The prefix length associated with this prefix. For IPv4 active subscriber session, the prefix length is always 32.

rbnSubsActiveIpAddrDescr.name: rbnSubsActiveIpAddrDescr
rbnSubsActiveIpAddrDescr.description: Human readable textual format of IP address.

rbnSubsClearSubscriberName.name: rbnSubsClearSubscriberName
rbnSubsClearSubscriberName.description: Setting this object to the subscriber name will clear all the sessions associated with the subscriber. In the case of PPP circuit, the PPP state machinery attempts to renegotiate and re-authenticate a new session with the remote peer on the circuit. In the case of RFC 1483 and RFC 1490 encapsulated circuits the circuit is brought down and then back up and an attempt is made to re-authenticate the subscriber bound to the circuit. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

rbnSubsClearSessionId.name: rbnSubsClearSessionId
rbnSubsClearSessionId.description: A set of this object will clear the subscriber session identified by this value. In the case of PPP circuit, the PPP state machinery attempts to renegotiate and re-authenticate a new session with the remote peer on the circuit. In the case of RFC 1483 and RFC 1490 encapsulated circuits the circuit is brought down and then back up and an attempt is made to re-authenticate the subscriber bound to the circuit. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

rbnSubsBounceName.name: rbnSubsBounceName
rbnSubsBounceName.description: Each circuit using CLIPS encapsulation used by the named subscriber is brought down and immediately recreated using the RADIUS Access- Accept attributes. Any other circuit encapsulation type is cleared. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

rbnSubsBounceSessionId.name: rbnSubsBounceSessionId
rbnSubsBounceSessionId.description: The circuit using CLIPS encapsulation identified by the RADIUS Acct-Session-Id is brought down and immediately recreated using the RADIUS Access-Accept attributes. Any other circuit encapsulation type is cleared. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

rbnSubsReauthRadiusIndex.name: rbnSubsReauthRadiusIndex
rbnSubsReauthRadiusIndex.description: An unsigned integer identifying a set of subscribers defined at the RADIUS server which are to be re-authorized. The source of this value and the set of subscribers to be re-authorized are defined outside the context of this mib module. An get of this attribute returns 0.

rbnSubsReauthRadiusID.name: rbnSubsReauthRadiusID
rbnSubsReauthRadiusID.description: An octet string identifying a set of subscribers defined at the RADIUS server which are to be re-authorized. The source of this value and the set of subscribers to be re-authorized are defined outside the context of this mib module. This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

rbnSubsReauthName.name: rbnSubsReauthName
rbnSubsReauthName.description: Used to reauthorize all of the active sessions associated with the given subscriber in the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3). This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

rbnSubsReauthSessionId.name: rbnSubsReauthSessionId
rbnSubsReauthSessionId.description: Used to reauthorize the active session identified by the value of this object and the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3). This object returns a zero-length string when queried.

rbnSubsClearReason.name: rbnSubsClearReason
rbnSubsClearReason.description: An unsigned integer value which may be included in the set request for rbnSubsClearSubscriberName, rbnSubsClearSessionId, rbnSubsBounceName, rbnSubsBounceSessionId, or any other objects define under the rbnSubsClear OID node. The use of this object value is implementation dependent. This object returns 0 when queried.

rbnSubsCntxtCountTable.name: rbnSubsCntxtCountTable
rbnSubsCntxtCountTable.description: This table contains counts of active subscribers by context name. Unlike any of the other tables in this mib module, all rows in this table are accessible when the context 'local' is specified in the snmp message, unless restricted by entries in the vacmAccessTable. Snmp requests using other contexts shall return only the row which matches the context.

rbnSubsCntxtCountEntry.name: rbnSubsCntxtCountEntry
rbnSubsCntxtCountEntry.description: The conceptual row containing the count of active subscribers for each context.

rbnSubsCntxtCount.name: rbnSubsCntxtCount
rbnSubsCntxtCount.description: The count of active subscribers with either IPv4 or IPv6 or both stack UP.

rbnSubsCntxtIp4OnlyCount.name: rbnSubsCntxtIp4OnlyCount
rbnSubsCntxtIp4OnlyCount.description: The count of IPv4 active subscribers which are authorized for only IPv4 protocol stack. This counter does not include subscribers authorized for dual IPv4/IPv6 protocol stack.

rbnSubsCntxtIp6OnlyCount.name: rbnSubsCntxtIp6OnlyCount
rbnSubsCntxtIp6OnlyCount.description: The count of IPv6 active subscribers which are authorized for only IPv6 protocol stack. This counter does not include subscribers authorized for dual IPv4/IPv6 protocol stack.

rbnSubsCntxtDualCount.name: rbnSubsCntxtDualCount
rbnSubsCntxtDualCount.description: The count of active subscribers which are authorized for both IPv4 and IPv6 for the context. At any time either one or both stacks may be UP.

rbnSubsCntxtLacCount.name: rbnSubsCntxtLacCount
rbnSubsCntxtLacCount.description: The count of active LAC subscribers.

rbnSubsEncapsCountTable.name: rbnSubsEncapsCountTable
rbnSubsEncapsCountTable.description: This table contains counts of active subscribers by encapsulation type.

rbnSubsEncapsCountEntry.name: rbnSubsEncapsCountEntry
rbnSubsEncapsCountEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnSubsEncapsCountTable.

rbnSubsEncapsulationType.name: rbnSubsEncapsulationType
rbnSubsEncapsulationType.description: This object identifies the type of encapsulation the subscriber is using. Note that 'ppp' includes all types of supported ppp, excluding pppoe.

rbnSubsEncapsCount.name: rbnSubsEncapsCount
rbnSubsEncapsCount.description: The count of active subscribers for the encapsulation type.

rbnSubsIPv6PktsReceived.description: The number of IPv6 packets received by the circuit. This counter includes multicast activity.

rbnSubsProfileCountTable.name: rbnSubsProfileCountTable
rbnSubsProfileCountTable.description: This table contains counts of active subscribers by encapsulation type.

rbnSubsProfileCountEntry.name: rbnSubsProfileCountEntry
rbnSubsProfileCountEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnSubsProfileCountTable.

rbnSubsProfileName.name: rbnSubsProfileName
rbnSubsProfileName.description: The profile name which applies to a set of subscribers.

rbnSubsProfileCount.name: rbnSubsProfileCount
rbnSubsProfileCount.description: The count of active subscribers for the profile name.

rbnSubsMaxSupportedSessions.name: rbnSubsMaxSupportedSessions
rbnSubsMaxSupportedSessions.description: The maximum number of active subscriber sessions that are supported on the SmartEdge router.

rbnSubsLicensedSessions.name: rbnSubsLicensedSessions
rbnSubsLicensedSessions.description: The number of licensed subscriber sessions on the SmartEdge router.

rbnSubsActiveSessions.name: rbnSubsActiveSessions
rbnSubsActiveSessions.description: The number of active subscriber sessions on the SmartEdge router.

rbnSubsCapacityPercentageUsed.name: rbnSubsCapacityPercentageUsed
rbnSubsCapacityPercentageUsed.description: The percentage of licensed subscriber sessions in use on the SmartEdge router. This value is computed as: if rbnSubsLicensedSessions equals 0 then if rbnSubsActiveSessions equals 0 then 0 else 100 else MIN((rbnSubsActiveSessions * 100)/rbnSubsLicensedSessions), 100).

rbnSubsServiceVolumeTable.name: rbnSubsServiceVolumeTable
rbnSubsServiceVolumeTable.description: This table specifies service volume information on the subscriber circuits. It contains the volume octet counts for each active subscriber session for which the service is active. All MIB objects defined in the table are viewed within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).

rbnSubsServiceVolumeEntry.name: rbnSubsServiceVolumeEntry
rbnSubsServiceVolumeEntry.description: A conceptual row in the RbnSubsServiceVolumeTable. Each row contains the service volume limit and volume octet count for each active service session.

rbnSubsServiceVolumeLimitIn.name: rbnSubsServiceVolumeLimitIn
rbnSubsServiceVolumeLimitIn.description: The volume limit in kilobytes (KB) allowed for the subscriber service to input (or receive) for this subscriber. If the value is 0, then there is no limit.

rbnSubsServiceVolumeLimitOut.name: rbnSubsServiceVolumeLimitOut
rbnSubsServiceVolumeLimitOut.description: The volume limit in kilobytes (KB) allowed for the subscriber service to output (or transmit) for this subscriber. If the value is 0, then there is no limit.

rbnSubsServiceActiveTime.name: rbnSubsServiceActiveTime
rbnSubsServiceActiveTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the service became active for this subscriber. If sysUpTime is reset to zero as a result of a reinitialization of the network management (sub)system, then the values of all TimeStamp objects are also reset.

rbnSubsServicesEntry.description: A conceptual row in the rbnSubsServicesTable.

rbnSubsNotifyEnable.name: rbnSubsNotifyEnable
rbnSubsNotifyEnable.description: This object will provide a mechanism for enabling and disabling subscriber notifications. A value of 1 (true) indicates that subscriber notifications are enabled. A value of 2 (false) indicates that subscriber notifications are disabled.

rbnSubsConfigErrorMsgs.name: rbnSubsConfigErrorMsgs
rbnSubsConfigErrorMsgs.description: Detailed error messages that describes the mis-configured attributes that failed authentication.

rbnSubsConfigErrorEvent.name: rbnSubsConfigErrorEvent
